      <description>Herman Kohlmeyer was a New Orleans businessman and friend of Gillis Long.
            He employed Long with Kohlmeyer &amp; Co., his investment banking firm, between 1968 and
            1971. Gillis Long (1923-1985) was representative for the 8th U.S. Congressional District
            of Louisiana in 1963-1965 and 1973-1985. He ran unsuccessfully for governor of Louisiana
            in 1964 and 1971.</description>
